<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">No. 217</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">840B.062/4–1851: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iceland (<persName corresp="#p_LEB1" type="from">Lawson</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret   priority</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reykjavik</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-18T18:00:00+00:00">April
                                        18, 1951—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>210. Inform Mitchell Defense.<note n="1" xml:id="d217fn1">The message
                                    was relayed to the Department of Defense on April 19 at 1
                                    a.m.</note> Fon Min has just informed me of govt’s great concern
                                possibility Commie directed strike set for May 18 which he says cld
                                easily take on character of general strike. Said govt as well as
                                social dems taken by surprise but will do everything possible
                                prevent serious widespread strikes.</p>
                            <p>He very fearful US troops will arrive here near that date which he
                                thinks wld be embarrassing us as well as Ice Govt, especially if
                                there port difficulties re off-loading our equipment, supplies etc.
                                He suggests date not later than May 3. Can we meet that date having
                                troops, as well as survey party alerted to meet that date when
                                confirmed? I recommend we make every effort.</p>
                            <p>Fon Min confident agreement will be signed in plenty of time to
                                permit such programing.</p>
                            <p>Pls comment soonest.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LEB1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lawson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>